### Page Types Under This Template

1. **Algemene Voorwaarden** (Terms & Conditions)
2. **Privacybeleid** (Privacy Policy)
3. **Licentie** (Business License/Compliance)
4. **Cookiebeleid** (Cookie Policy)

### Required Sections (In Order)

#### 1. Breadcrumbs
- Format: Home > [Page Title]

#### 2. Header
- **H1**: Document title
- **Last updated**: Visible date
- **Version**: If applicable

#### 3. Table of Contents (For Long Documents)
- **Format**: Linked list of sections
- **Threshold**: Include if document has 5+ sections

#### 4. Content Sections
- **Format**: Numbered sections with H2 headers
- **Structure**: 
  - Use clear section titles
  - Keep paragraphs short
  - Use bullets for lists of items/rights
- **Language**: Plain Dutch/English where possible; legal terms where required

#### 5. Contact for Questions
- **Format**: Simple text block at end
- **Content**: "Vragen over deze voorwaarden? Neem contact op via [email]"

### SEO Requirements
- **Schema**: WebPage (legal pages typically don't need special schema)
- **Indexing**: Generally index, but consider noindex for very boilerplate policies
- **Canonical**: Self-referencing

### Content Guidelines
- Write for readability while maintaining legal accuracy
- Use headers to break up dense text
- Highlight user rights and obligations
- Include effective date and update history
- Link to related policies where referenced

### Legal Page Specific Requirements

**Algemene Voorwaarden**:
- Service description and scope
- Booking and cancellation terms
- Payment terms
- Liability limitations
- Dispute resolution

**Privacybeleid**:
- What data is collected
- How data is used
- Data retention periods
- User rights (GDPR compliance)
- Cookie policy reference

**Licentie**:
- Business registration details
- Compliance statements
- Regulatory information
- Trust signals (certifications, memberships)

---

## Technical Content Requirements

### All Pages Must Include

| Element | Requirement |
|---------|-------------|
| H1 | Exactly one, containing primary keyword |
| Meta title | 50-60 characters, keyword-optimized |
| Meta description | 150-160 characters, include CTA intent |
| Canonical | Self-referencing |
| Hreflang | NL/EN alternate for bilingual pages |
| Schema markup | Page-type appropriate (FAQ, LocalBusiness, etc.) |

### Forbidden Patterns

- Keyword stuffing in headers
- Invisible text or hidden content
- Doorway page patterns (thin content redirecting to main page)
- Duplicate content across locations without unique sections
- External links to competitors
- Auto-generated content without human review

---

## Quality Checklist Per Page

Before marking any page complete, verify:

- [ ] Word count within specification
- [ ] H1 contains primary keyword naturally
- [ ] Required unique content section present
- [ ] FAQ section structured for schema markup
- [ ] Internal links preserved from legacy high-value pathways
- [ ] No template filler content remaining
- [ ] CTA present and actionable
- [ ] Mobile-scannable (short paragraphs, headers, bullets)
- [ ] Metadata optimized per Keyword Strategy
- [ ] Technical SEO elements correct

---

## Content Extraction Workflow

### Step 1: Identify Unique Content
From Firecrawl/WordPress extraction, mark:
- Location-specific information
- Genuine testimonials or reviews
- Unique FAQ questions
- Differentiating claims (verifiable)

### Step 2: Map to New Structure
Place extracted unique content into appropriate section per this specification.

### Step 3: Write Missing Sections
Create new unique content for required sections not covered by extraction.

### Step 4: Remove Filler
Delete all template text, generic descriptions, and repeated content.

### Step 5: Validate
Run quality checklist before marking complete.
